# 🖥️ Marvellous Customised Virtual File System (CVFS)

A **Customised Virtual File System (CVFS)** implemented in **C**, simulating the core functionality of an operating system's file system. This project provides an in-memory file system with support for file creation, deletion, reading, writing, permission management, and a command-line shell interface.

It is designed to help understand the internal working of file systems, inode management, file descriptors, and operating system concepts.

---

# ✨ Features

- In-Memory Virtual File System
- Linux-like Command Line Interface
- File Creation and Deletion
- Read and Write Operations
- Permission Management (Read / Write)
- Inode-Based File Management
- Super Block Management
- User File Descriptor Table (UFDT)
- Dynamic Memory Allocation
- Error Handling with Custom Error Codes

---

# 🏗️ System Architecture

```
                    User Shell
                        │
                        ▼
              Command Interpreter
                        │
        ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐
        ▼               ▼               ▼
     SuperBlock       UFDT          DILB (Inodes)
                        │
                        ▼
                  File Table
                        │
                        ▼
                   File Buffer
```

---

# 📂 Project Components

## Boot Block

Stores boot information about the virtual operating system.

---

## Super Block

Maintains overall file system information.

- Total Inodes
- Free Inodes

---

## DILB (Disk Inode List Block)

A linked list containing all available inodes.

Each inode stores:

- File Name
- Inode Number
- File Size
- Actual File Size
- File Type
- Permission
- Reference Count
- Data Buffer

---

## UFDT (User File Descriptor Table)

Stores information about currently opened files.

Each entry contains:

- Read Offset
- Write Offset
- Access Mode
- Pointer to Inode

---

# 📋 Supported Commands

| Command | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `creat <filename> <permission>` | Create a new file |
| `write <fd>` | Write data into a file |
| `read <fd> <size>` | Read data from a file |
| `unlink <filename>` | Delete a file |
| `ls` | Display all files |
| `man <command>` | Show manual page |
| `help` | Display available commands |
| `clear` | Clear terminal |
| `exit` | Exit the virtual file system |

---

# 🔐 File Permissions

| Value | Permission |
|--------|------------|
| 1 | Read |
| 2 | Write |
| 3 | Read + Write |

---

# 🖥️ Example Session

```text
Marvellous CVFS : > creat Demo.txt 3
File gets successfully created with FD 3

Marvellous CVFS : > write 3
Enter the data that you want to write :
Hello World

11 bytes gets successfully written

Marvellous CVFS : > read 3 11

Data from file is :
Hello World

Marvellous CVFS : > ls

Inode   File Name      Size
1       Demo.txt       11

Marvellous CVFS : > unlink Demo.txt

File gets successfully deleted
```

